    {"title": "Buttery Lemon-Herb-Rubbed Roast Chicken", "page": 595, "chapter": "Roasts", "fitsMenu": "chicken (favorite)", "scanned": true, "makes": "3 or 4 servings", "captured": {"ingredients":["1/4 cup fresh parsley leaves","6 fresh sage leaves","1 tbsp fresh rosemary leaves","1 scallion, roughly chopped","1 medium garlic clove, minced (~1 tsp)","2 tsp kosher salt","1 tsp freshly ground black pepper","1 tbsp grated lemon zest (from 1 lemon)","2 tbsp unsalted butter","1 whole chicken, 3.5 to 4 lb"],"steps":["Process the parsley, sage, rosemary, scallion, garlic, salt, pepper, lemon zest, and butter into a smooth paste.","Loosen the skin from the breasts and thighs and rub the herb-butter paste all over and under the skin.","Roast following the Simple Whole Roast Chicken method (p.594), skipping its step 2."],"tips":["Butter under the skin trades a little crispness for big flavor - compensate by dry-brining and air-drying the bird uncovered overnight (p.579) for the juiciest meat and crispest skin.","Get the paste under the skin, not just on top, so it seasons the meat directly."]}},
